ing org.eclipse.rdf4j.sail.spin.SpifSailTest\nTests run: 13, Failures: 1, Errors: 0, Skipped: 0, Time elapsed: 48.194 sec <<< FAILURE! - in org.eclipse.rdf4j.sail.spin.SpifSailTest\nrunTests(org.eclipse.rdf4j.sail.spin.SpifSailTest)  Time elapsed: 4.219 sec  <<< FAILURE!\njava.lang.AssertionError: http://spinrdf.org/spif#Test-dateFormat-1 expected:<\"February 13, 2008\"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string>> but was:<\"febbraio 13, 2008\"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string>>\n    at org.junit.Assert.fail(Assert.java:88)\n    at org.junit.Assert.failNotEquals(Assert.java:834)\n    at org.junit.Assert.assertEquals(Assert.java:118)\n    at org.eclipse.rdf4j.sail.spin.SpifSailTest.runTests(SpifSailTest.java:94)\n```\n\nThe actual value contains the word \"febbraio\", which is the Italian word for February. \n\nThe code below should be the failing test case.\n\n```\nspif:Test-dateFormat-1\n  rdf:type spl:TestCase ;\n  spl:testExpression [\n      rdf:type spif:dateFormat ;\n      arg:date \"2008-02-13\"^^xsd:date ;\n      arg:pattern \"MMMMMMMMM dd, yyyy\" ;\n    ] ;\n  spl:testResult \"febbraio 13, 2008\"^^xsd:string ;\n  rdfs:label \"Test-date format\"^^xsd:string ;\n.\n```\n\nIndeed, it requires that the structured date `\"2008-02-13\"^^xsd:date` is formatted according to the template `\"MMMMMMMMM dd, yyyy\"`.\n\nThe implementation of `spif:dateFormat` seems to use the default locale, which explains the observed behavior.\n\nIf the implementation is right, then the tests should be updated to avoid the failure.\n","closed_by":{"login":"abrokenjester","id":728776,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcyODc3Ng==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/728776?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/abrokenjester","html_url":"https://github.com/abrokenjester","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/abrokenjester/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/abrokenjester/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com